article.headline: S. Illinois 10, W. Illinois 9
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- Quarterback Nick Hill scored a touchdown in the fourth quarter to give Southern Illinois a narrow 10-9 victory over Western Illinois on Saturday. Hill completed 22-of-29 passes for 250 yards for the Salukis (8-1, 4-1 Gateway). His top targets were Justin Allen, who had five receptions for 62 yards, and Phil Goforth, who had five receptions for 44 yards. John Randle rushed for 42 yards for the Salukis. Leatherneck (6-4, 3-2) running back Herb Donaldson rushed for 147 yards. Quarterback Matt Barr completed 16-of-25 passes for 208 yards for Western Illinois; he also rushed for 71 yards and scored one touchdown. Western Illinois led 9-3 at the half and neither team scored in the third quarter. Hill led an 80-yard drive in the fourth before carrying the ball 1 yard and in for score; Kyle Dougherty kicked the extra point to put the Salukis ahead for good.
